HEADWORD: Muscardin
<hw>Mus"car*din</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>muscadin</ets> a musk-scented lozenge, fr. <ets>muscade</ets>
nutmeg, fr. L. <ets>muscus</ets> musk. See <er>Muscadel</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The common European dormouse; -- so named from
its odor.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>muscadine</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Muscardine</ent>⟦br⟧
